<taxonomicName box="[291,555,1820,1842]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Decoradrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="119" pageNumber="120" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="harlequina" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[291,555,1820,1842]" italics="true" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">Decoradrillia harlequina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[574,707,1820,1842]" pageId="119" pageNumber="120" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[723,864,1821,1842]" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">Upper panel</emphasis>
. Figs. 1–3: holotype, Devil's Bay, Grenada (USNM 1291335). Fig. 1: ventral, lateral &amp; dorsal views; Fig. 2: enlarged view of protoconch (not to scale); Fig. 3: apical view, V = varix, L = edge of outer lip. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[440,575,1882,1903]" pageId="119" pageNumber="120">Lower panel</emphasis>
. Fig. 4: paratype, from the type locality (USNM 1291336); Fig. 5: Man of War Bay, Tobago I., Trinidad &amp; Tobago (ANSP 464967); Figs. 6–7: paratypes, Annas Shoal, St. Georges, Grenada (P. Williams coll.); Figs. 8–9: Hollandes Cays, San Blas Is., Panama (P. Williams coll.); Fig. 10: San Pedro, Ambergris Cay, Belize (P. Williams coll.); Figs. 11–12: Mt. Irving Bay, Tobago I., Trinidad &amp; Tobago (P. Williams coll.); Fig. 13: paratype, Union I., St. Vincent &amp; the Grenadines (UF 496635); Fig. 14: St Martin (MNHN, ex J. Colomb coll.).
</paragraph>
